RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Imprison
<hw>Im*pris"on</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Imprisoned</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Imprisoning</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE.
<ets>enprisonen</ets>, OF. <ets>enprisoner</ets>, F.
<ets>emprisonner</ets>; pref. <ets>en-</ets> (L. <ets>in</ets>) + F. &
OF. <ets>prison</ets>. See <er>Prison</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
put in prison or jail; To arrest and detain in custody; to
confine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He <qex>imprisoned</qex> was in chains remediless.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To limit, restrain, or confine in any way.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Try to <qex>imprison</qex> the resistless wind.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To incarcerate; confine; immure.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Imprisoner</ent>⟦br⟧
